---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="The Upper Room — what this is and why it exists." path="/about/">
  <div class="container-upper py-12 max-w-prose-wide" data-pagefind-body>

    <div class="mb-10">
      <span class="text-label text-gold-600 block mb-2">The Upper Room</span>
      <h1 class="font-display text-display-md font-bold text-brown-900 mb-4">About</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-6 font-serif text-brown-800 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p class="dropcap">
        The Upper Room is a quiet place on the internet — a devotional reading companion
        for Christians who want to read Scripture, encounter the great saints of the faith,
        and be nourished in their walk with God.
      </p>

      <p>
        The name comes from Acts 1:13 — the room where the disciples gathered after the
        Ascension, waiting in prayer. It has become a symbol of faithful waiting, communal
        devotion, and the kind of quiet attentiveness that God honors.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-brown-900 mt-10 mb-4">What You'll Find Here</h2>

      <p>The Upper Room is designed for the Christian who wants to go deeper:</p>

      <ul class="space-y-3 pl-0 list-none">
        <li class="flex gap-3 text-base">
          <span class="text-gold-500 font-semibold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✦</span>
          <span>Daily quotes from the communion of saints — Spurgeon, Lewis, Augustine, Owen, Calvin, Keller, Ortlund, and many more</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3 text-base">
          <span class="text-gold-500 font-semibold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✦</span>
          <span>The ESV Bible reader with a clean, focused interface designed for reading, not scanning</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3 text-base">
          <span class="text-gold-500 font-semibold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✦</span>
          <span>The Archive — classic devotional literature organized by theme: grace, justification, prayer, suffering, sanctification</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3 text-base">
          <span class="text-gold-500 font-semibold flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">✦</span>
          <span>Studies — topical theological outlines for deeper engagement with Scripture and the Christian tradition</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-brown-900 mt-10 mb-4">The Design</h2>
      <p>
        The Upper Room is intentionally analog in feel — warm parchment tones, book-weight
        typography set in EB Garamond and Playfair Display, gold accents that recall
        illuminated manuscripts. No notification badges. No dark patterns. Just reading.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-brown-900 mt-10 mb-4">ESV Bible</h2>
      <p>
        Scripture is drawn from the English Standard Version (ESV), a modern translation
        prized for its literal accuracy and literary beauty. API access provided by
        <a href="https://api.esv.org" class="text-gold-600 hover:underline">Crossway</a>.
      </p>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-gold-500 pl-6 py-2 my-8">
        <p class="italic text-brown-800">
          "All Scripture is breathed out by God and profitable for teaching, for reproof,
          for correction, and for training in righteousness, that the man of God may be
          complete, equipped for every good work." — 2 Timothy 3:16-17
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
